    <h2 id="Profile">Why do you need all this information in my profile?</h2>
    <p>We need this information for many reasons.  We explain this in detail here what we collect and why we do so: </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Personal information: We work with indiviual freelancers, not with companies; We don't share your personal information with our customers, but we do share this with the Belgian tax authorities if they audit our payments. So your personal information has to be real and true. Your address will be checked in Google Maps. Your mail address is used to retrieve your PIN and to verify any changes you make to your profile. If this is wrong or false, you will lose access to your account. </li>
        <li>Professional information: we work with all professions who can contribute value to our datasets. We need to know where you work, what languages you can help us with and what is your professional background.</li>
        <li>Payment information: we only send work to people we can pay. So we need to know how we can pay you, and what kind of payment that will be: a personal payment or a payment to a company account; Typically you will generate a NOTE for a personal payment, and an INVOICE to receive a payment on a compnay account.</li>
        <li>Non Disclosure Agreement: you can only work for us IF you agree to this correct professional behaviour. If you disagree with one of these rules, don't create an account, or delete it. Deleting an account does not discharge you of the rules you agreed to before; It will however delete your account on our servers. This cannot be undone. </li>
    </ul>
    <p> We comply to the European GDRP.    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>We don't rent or trade email lists or any other information with other organisations and businesses. </li>
        <li>Our customers don’t know who works on their research jobs. All we share with them is a unique freelancer number. They cannot find out who’s the person matching that unique identifier.</li>
        <li>We protect your personal data in the best way we can: all communication between you and our server is encrypted, and the very little personal information that we do store in a database, is encrypted inside the database as well. Once you start working on our jobs, we compare this information with the information stored in your local profile file. When this matches, our tools will work. When it doesn’t match, none of our tools will work.</li>
        <li>You are entitled to view, amend, or delete the personal information that we hold. Email your request to our data protection officer: Gert Van Assche.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>At Datamundi, we are committed to maintaining the trust and confidence of our visitors to our web site. In particular, we want you to know that Datamundi is not in the business of selling, renting or trading email lists with other companies and businesses for marketing purposes. In this help, we’ve provided lots of detailed information on when and why we collect your personal information, how we use it, the limited conditions under which we may disclose it to others and how we keep it secure.<br>
