    <h2 id="whatWeDo">What do we do as Datamundi</h2>
    <p>We negotiate with our customers about cost and deadlines, about data formats and job requirements.</p>
    <p>We translate the requirements into actionable instructions. If the instructions according to our freelancers need to be changed, we discuss this with our customers.</p>
    <p>We try to get correct estimates of the work to be done, so our freelancers get a correct and fair value for their work.</p>
    <p>We create work types to streamline similar jobs for different customers, so our freelancers don’t need to learn how to use them for every new job.</p>
    <p>We test our freelancers, and select the most fit ones for each job.</p>
    <p>We build tools on this job portal to get the work done through these work types.</p>
    <p>We convert customer data to a job format, and we consolidate the job data into data formats our customers can use.</p>
    <p>We guide the freelancers, answer their questions as fast and accurate as we can. </p>
    <p>We monitor the work done by our freelancers, and make sure we can meet the deadlines.</p>
    <p>We check the work before we deliver to our customer.</p>
    <p>We handle customer complaints before we inform the freelancers about this.</p>
    <p>We scale our team and tools in order to handle the ever growing list of supported language pairs and work types.</p>
    <p>We pay our freelancers the same week we receive their invoice. This is at least 6 weeks before we get paid ourselves. This way we pre-finance the project of our customers and we don’t make our freelancers wait for their reward.</p>
    <p>We figure out the best payment options, per country; If we can, we also take care of the payment fees.</p>
    <p>We redo the work at no extra cost if our customers are not happy with the quality we deliver.</p>
    <p>On our <a href="https://datamundi.space/" target="_blank">homepage</a> you can read about our work types.</p>
